The paper discusses the use of swarm intelligence, specifically ant colony optimization, for routing in mobile ad hoc networks (MANETs). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also mentions the use of bio-inspired techniques, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The development of special routing algorithms for MANETs involves the use of optimization techniques, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the self-organizing dynamics of ant societies, which falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of different routing algorithms, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
